<paragraph id="8BB7368AD85CFFD33CB4FBA3362EFF0F" blockId="9.[151,1059,1049,1129]" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D85CFFD33E0BFBA330BBFF48" box="[552,644,1049,1070]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">apunctus</emphasis>
, is a Latin compound name that stems from the prefix – a (= without) and the noun 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D85CFFD33E44FB8D3081FF2A" box="[615,702,1079,1100]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">punctum</emphasis>
(= dot); in reference to the lack of a dark spot on the pronotal disc, very characteristic of many males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D85CFFD33F7AFBE93185FF0E" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" box="[857,954,1107,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="970" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D85CFFD33F7AFBE93185FF0E" box="[857,954,1107,1128]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Perilypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
